EPISTLE VI

Nothing is known of the Numicius to whom this Epistle is addressed, nor is there any hint to assist us 111 determining the date. Its general purpose is to recommend a. philosophie calm as the true way of regarding the various objects of human desire. But from line 31 to the end Horace adopts a tone of strong irony, urging Numicius, if he will not accept this theory of life, to pursue with resolute energy whatever end he may choose to propose to himself.
